Package it.polimi.ingsw.view.interfaces

Interface GameEventHandler

All Known Subinterfaces:
UI
All Known Implementing Classes:
CLI, ConfigController, Controller, GameController, JoinLobbyController, LobbiesListController, LobbyController, MainController, MenuController, SetupPhaseController
public interface GameEventHandler
This interface represents the game event handler, which is used to handle the game events coming from the server. This interface is implemented by the UI abstract class.

    • handleDrawnGoldDeckCardEvent

      void handleDrawnGoldDeckCardEvent(PlayerToken playerToken, int drawnCardId, boolean deckEmptied, Integer nextCardId, int handIndex)
      This method handles the received update of a drawn card from the gold deck
      Parameters:
      playerToken - the token of the player who draws the card from the gold deck
      drawnCardId - the drawn card id
      deckEmptied - a flag that is true if the deck is now empty, false otherwise
      nextCardId - the id of the next card; null if there is no next card
      handIndex - the position (0,1,2) of the drawn card in the player hand
